      <div class="comment-author vcard">
         <img alt='' src='http://1.gravatar.com/avatar/3bd36cb0c1342448e34ad2cb90f8a5bf?s=48&amp;d=identicon&amp;r=G' class='avatar avatar-48 photo' height='48' width='48' />         <cite class="fn"><a href='http://twomoreseconds.com' rel='external nofollow' class='url'>Erin</a>:</cite>
      </div>
      
      <div class="comment-meta commentmetadata"><a href="http://www.make-it-do.com/cook-it-bake-it/moms-scones/#comment-69565">June 14, 2011 at 11:22 AM</a></div>

      <p>Oh Calli this is hilarious &#8211; we also had these kind of scones growing up and I have a treasured recipe book that my mom typed up for me where this exact same recipe appears front and center.  :]  I seriously LOVE these scones, and love that my sons are beginning to love them too.  They know it&#8217;s a special night if I say it&#8217;s scone night for dinner.  And I don&#8217;t know what anyone is talking about &#8211; those crusty, flaky things are NOT scones! ;]</p>

      <div class="reply">
         <a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='/cook-it-bake-it/moms-scones/?replytocom=69565#respond' onclick='return addComment.moveForm("comment-69565", "69565", "respond", "13660")'>Reply</a>      </div>

